# Project Stack — Do Not Suggest Alternatives

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15+ (App Router only — never suggest Pages Router)
- Payload CMS 3.x (our headless CMS — never suggest Contentful, Sanity, Strapi)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Vercel for deployment
- React Server Components by default

## Code Style
- Use functional components with TypeScript interfaces
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use kebab-case for directories (e.g., components/hero-section)
- PascalCase for component files
- Use `const` arrow functions for components
- Never use `any` — use `unknown` or define a type

## Component Rules
- Server Components by default — only add `'use client'` when needed
- Minimize 'use client', 'useEffect', and 'useState'
- Wrap client components in Suspense with fallback
- Use dynamic loading for non-critical components

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS utility classes only — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Mobile-first responsive design (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)
- Use CSS variables for theme colors
- Ensure WCAG AA color contrast (4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for large text)

## Performance
- Optimize images: use next/image with WebP, include size data, lazy load
- Optimize Web Vitals (LCP, CLS, INP)
- Eliminate async waterfalls — use Promise.all for parallel data fetching
- Use Suspense boundaries for streaming

## SEO
- Every page must have proper metadata (title, description, Open Graph)
- Use semantic HTML (<nav>, <main>, <article>, <section>)
- Implement structured data (JSON-LD) where appropriate
- Ensure all images have descriptive alt text

## Accessibility
- Proper ARIA attributes on interactive elements
- Keyboard navigation support for all interactive components
- Visible focus states
- Skip-to-content link on every page

## Payload CMS Conventions
- Collections use kebab-case slugs
- Use Payload's built-in access control — never bypass
- Rich text fields use the Lexical editor
- Media uploads go through Payload's upload collection
- Use Payload's local API for server-side data fetching
